        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 21 at 1:24PM CDT by NWS Louisville KY</headline>
        <description>At 124 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles southwest of Glasgow, moving southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lucas, Peter Creek, Cooktown, and Roseville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
